{"questionId":"10255","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Xylene is a derivative of benzene. One isomer is 1,4-dimethylbenzene.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3218a8f6e8c22aa4d6cf6d6eaa537e3692f3e50f.png\" alt=\"\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The organic product is not optically active. Discuss whether or not the organic product is a racemic mixture.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">no <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>there is no chiral carbon</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">no <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>there is no carbon with four different substituents/groups <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept “no <strong>AND</strong> no asymmetric carbon<br>atom”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10255","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ1.1e","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The organic product is not optically active. Discuss whether or not the organic product is a racemic mixture.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry","20.3 Stereoisomerism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}